## Rule: Alpine.js Toast Behavior

Use Alpine.js to handle toast display, auto-dismiss, and animations.

- All toast notifications must use Alpine.js for their lifecycle and visibility.
- Use `x-data="{ show: true }"` and `x-init="setTimeout(() => show = false, 5000)"` to auto-hide.
- Wrap the toast in `x-show="show"` and apply `x-transition` for fade-in/out.
- Allow manual dismissal with a button `@click="show = false"`.

### Example

```html
<div
  x-data="{ show: true }"
  x-init="setTimeout(() => show = false, 5000)"
  x-show="show"
  x-transition
>
  <div class="toast bg-green-500 text-white p-4 rounded shadow">
    <span>Password cracked: `hunter2`</span>
    <button class="ml-4" @click="show = false">&times;</button>
  </div>
</div>
```

